                <h1>Hostel<h1>
                        <p>The hostel facility for both Boys' and Girls' are available within the campus and their
                            administration
                            centrally lies with the Dean, Administration of the college. The in-campus hostel provides a
                            much better
                            learning environment, as most of the time students resort to collaborative learning for
                            covering up
                            their syllabi and other project works. Staying within comfort and high-security zone of
                            college campus
                            significantly enhances the performance level of students in University examinations and
                            various
                            placement drives. Evening classes for self-study and doubt clearings are regularly carried
                            out which
                            turns out to be one of the major advantages, most of the time parents look forward to while
                            putting
                            their wards in campus hostel. Besides, during weekends, cultural programs are arranged on
                            campus, in
                            order to provide a little relaxation from the busy and hectic schedules associated with
                            various academic
                            activities.</p>
                        <p><b> A massive accommodation infrastructure in the form of 5 in-campus hostels are available
                                catering to the need of 1200 and an odd(approx) number of students.</b></p>
            </div>
            <div class="rightside">
                <img src="/media/hostel3.png" alt="">
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="canteen">
            <div class="leftside1">
                <h1>Central Mess<h1></h1>
                    <img src="/media/canteen.png" alt="">
            </div>
            <div class="rightside1">
                <p>The institute is having its self-managed canteen, providing services to a mammoth gathering
                    of capacity 1000 at a time.
                    All type of food items and beverages are available and served to all stakeholders on paymeny
                    basis.
                    A 43 number of Central Mess staff remain in action throughout in providing quality and
                    hygienic services to the campus inmates day and night.</p>
            </div>
        </div>


        <div class="gym">
            <div class="leftside2">
                <h1>Multipurpose GYM<h1>
                        <p>A healthy body gives rise to a healthy mind and a healthy mind, in turn, gives rise to a
                            successful human being with tremendous potentials. Gandhi Engineering College(GEC,
                            Bhubaneswar) strongly believes in this ethos and has taken the multi-pronged approach in
                            ensuring a healthy body and a healthy mind of its students, faculty members, and staff.
                            Besides avenues for sports or games, students and staff are provided with ultra-modern Gym
                            facilities within the campus, which cater to the need for regular exercise and body-building
                            activities of the inmates. A regular Physical Education Teacher(PET) and a Gym instructor
                            remain in action throughout, in guiding and organizing several activities during the regular
                            timing of the institution. Separate timing slots are available for both Girls' and Boys' for
                            the smooth utilization of Gym..</p>
                        <p><b> A massive accommodation infrastructure in the form of 5 in-campus hostels are available
                                catering to the need of 1200 and an odd(approx) number of students.</b></p>
            </div>
            <div class="rightside2">
                <img src="/media/gm2.jpg" alt="">
            </div>
        </div>

